The former deputy senate president of Nigeria, Senator Ike Ekweremadu was remanded in police custody along with his wife, Beatrice Nwanneka Ekweremadu in the United Kingdom after bail denial for alleged case of child exploitation and organ harvest accusation; many people were of the opinion that the boy was lying against the senator and Aisha Yesufu reacted to their claims and opinions.
According to Aisha Yesufu, if the boy is lying, she said that the court will find out and that the Ekweremadu family is not detained in a country where the judicial system is based on sentiments. She also claimed that they have the money to afford the best lawyers. She said they will be vindicated but that it is the boy that is helpless at the moment if he is telling the truth.
She also asked the people why they are ready to believe that the boy is lying? She also claimed that money buys justice and that the Ekweremadu family can afford the best and most expensive lawyers in the world to prove it.
She was also of the opinion that there are people who sell their organs because of poverty but kicked against selling it under duress. She concluded by asking the people of they have even thought about the boy.



